RE|REG|A1125284|1299229|2698748|FCC|05/09/2016|0|CONDITION:  Grant of this FONSI is subject to the following conditions in order to avoid potential impact to the Whooping Crane, a federal-listed endangered species protected by the Endangered Species Act (ESA).
RE|REG|A1125284|1299229|2698748|FCC|05/09/2016|1|In accordance with the email, dated October 14, 2014, Frank Weaver, Fish & Wildlife Biologist, Texas Coastal Ecological Services Field Office, US Fish and Wildlife Service,  to Warren Watts.  San Antonio MTA, L.P. accepts this email as notification and
RE|REG|A1125284|1299229|2698748|FCC|05/09/2016|2|agrees to incorporate and follow the following conditions during the construction of the proposed tower. 1)	If equipment 15 feet high or higher is to be used during construction, it shall be put down at night and shall be marked during the day.
RE|REG|A1125284|1299229|2698748|FCC|05/09/2016|3|2)	Workers shall be educated on the potential for Whooping Cranes to migrate through the area, their federally endangered status, and their appearance. 3)	If a Whooping Crane is observed near the site and within 1000 feet of the construction area,
RE|REG|A1125284|1299229|2698748|FCC|05/09/2016|4|work will cease until the bird has moved beyond that distance or left the area. 4)	Whooping Crane sightings during construction shall be reported to the Corpus Christi FWS Office at (361) 994-9005.
