RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|3|during construction and when traveling onsite to avoid killing snakes. In addition, protecting burrows and leaving native vegetation as refugia onsite for indigo snakes displaced by construction activity can benefit this species.
RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|4|The eastern indigo snake is not likely to be adversely affected if the following measures are implemented for the project. 1) Burrows and onsite native vegetation should be protected. If such habitat must be disturbed, limit disturbance to a minimum.
RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|5|Maintain native vegetation onsite as refuges for the snake.
RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|6|2) Clearing and grading activities should be performed outside high activity months (June to November). Winter months (January to March) provide the best opportunity to initiate and complete construction activities that will not impact this species.
RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|7|3) Post informational signs containing the following information throughout the construction site and along any proposed access road: a) A description and picture of the eastern indigo snake, its habits, and protection under Federal Law;
RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|8|b) Instructions not to injure, harass, or kill this species; c) Directions to cease clearing activities and allow the eastern indigo snake sufficient time to move away from the site on its own before resuming clearing; and,
RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|9|d) Telephone numbers of pertinent agencies to be contacted if a dead eastern indigo snake is encountered.
RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|10|Dead, injured, or sick animals: If a dead, injured, or sick eastern indigo snake is found onsite, notification should be made to the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service: Georgia Ecological Services Field Office, 105 Westpark Dr. Westpark Center Suite D Athens,
RE|REG|A1161357|1029217|129395|FCC|04/20/2017|11|GA 30606-3175   phone (706) 613-9493.
