RE|REG|A1262156|1307208|2706904|FCC|08/23/2018|1|On May 17, 2018, BMA Towers, LLC (Applicant) filed ASR Application No. A1089974 for an unlit 170-foot tall lattice tower in New Meadows, Idaho.  On June 18, 2018, the Shoshone-Bannock Tribes (the Tribes) filed pleadings objecting to the project,
RE|REG|A1262156|1307208|2706904|FCC|08/23/2018|2|expressing concerns about potential environmental effects on historic and cultural properties.   Among other issues, the Tribes protested the applicant’s failure to accommodate a qualified archaeological monitor during ground disturbing activities,
RE|REG|A1262156|1307208|2706904|FCC|08/23/2018|3|disputed the adequacy of the Environmental Assessment, opposed the No Adverse Effect recommendation, and requested government-to-government consultation.  Subsequent consultation associated with the Commission’s Section 106 review process resulted in an
RE|REG|A1262156|1307208|2706904|FCC|08/23/2018|4|amended Memorandum of Agreement addressing the Tribes concerns which was agreed to by all the parties and fully executed on August 14, 2018.  No other outstanding environmental or historic preservation issues were raised in the pleadings. Therefore, we
RE|REG|A1262156|1307208|2706904|FCC|08/23/2018|5|consider the Shoshone-Bannock Tribes’ June 18, 2018 comments to be addressed and dismiss the filed objections.
