RE|REG|A1262960|1310702|2710399|FCC|06/06/2019|1|CONDITION: "In addition to the general conditions attached to the Nationwide Permit 12 and 14 permits, ACOE identified an additional special condition: “To reduce any potential adverse effects on the Federally threatened Northern
RE|REG|A1262960|1310702|2710399|FCC|06/06/2019|2|long-eared bat (Myotis septentrional), trees (woody steams > 3 inches Diameter at Breast Height) must not be cut between April 1 and September 30, of any year.”
