RE|REG|A1235078|1310704|2710401|FCC|06/06/2019|1|"This FONSI is conditioned on the June 22, 2018 USFWS letter stating tree removal must occur between October 31 and March 31 when bats are in hibernation, bright orange construction fencing and/or flagging (or similar) should be used to demarcate trees
RE|REG|A1235078|1310704|2710401|FCC|06/06/2019|2|to be protected compared with those to be cut prior to the initiation of any construction, and the number of lights will be limited, include motion sensors or timers, and be shielded to direct light down towards the ground and buildings."
