RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|2|overall height of the tower structure, and/or addition or modification of any transmitting antennas, be submitted to the Enforcement Bureau for review to determine if it will have an adverse impact on the Commission’s Powder Springs, GA monitoring station
RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|3|Special Conditions: 1. The authority granted herein is subject to the condition that the field strength of the fundamental signal in any channel produced by the permitted/licensed facility shall not exceed the following field strengths as measured at
RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|4|the Federal Communications Commission's Powder Springs, Georgia monitoring station located at coordinates 33-51-44.4 North, 84-43-25.8 West (NAD 83): a) 734 MHz to 746 MHz band: 260 mV/m b) 758 MHz to 768 MHz band: 301 mV/m
RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|5|c) 880 MHz to 885 MHz band: 634 mV/m 2. In the event that any of the respective field strength limits listed in items 1(a) through 1(f) above is exceeded, or if interference occurs to the monitoring, direction finding, or related operations of the
RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|6|Federal Communications Commission's Powder Springs, Georgia monitoring station due to intermodulation, spurious emissions, or any other reason related to the operation of the this transmitter, the permittee/licensee shall take such immediate corrective
RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|7|action as is necessary to eliminate the interference. This shall include responsibility for furnishing, installing and adjusting transmitter filter circuits, shielding, or other corrective devices. If these measures fail to eliminate interference to FCC
RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|8|operations caused by the presence of the permittee/licensee's signal, or if any of the field strengths exceeds the allowable limits, the permittee/licensee shall immediately reduce power to the extent necessary to eliminate the interference and /or
RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|9|comply with field strength limit(s). After determining this lower power level, the permittee/licensee shall immediately apply for a Special Temporary Authority (STA),or equivalent,and shall file an application to the Commission for the altered parameters.
RE|REG|A1168864|1314228|2714012|FCC|03/31/2020|10|3. The applicant shall advise the Enforcement Bureau’s Spectrum Enforcement Division, of the exact date when it intends to commence normal transmitter operations, and another notification when normal transmitter operations actually commence.
