RE|REG|A1180198|1317227|2717011|FCC|11/19/2020|2|and Wildlife Foundation of Florida’s conservation fund for the bonneted bat. To address the loss of scrub jay habitat, Martin County has committed to work with Jonathan Dickinson State Park to conduct habitat improvements for scrub jays. Habitat
RE|REG|A1180198|1317227|2717011|FCC|11/19/2020|3|improvement will consist of removing an infestation of cabbage palms as described in the Jonathan Dickinson State Park Cabbage Palm Mastication Project B13 B12 . The work will be completed prior to the 2021 scrub jay nesting season. However, if that is
RE|REG|A1180198|1317227|2717011|FCC|11/19/2020|4|not feasible, work will be conducted following the nesting season in 2021.
