RE|REG|A1273228|1319096|2718880|FCC|04/16/2021|1|This FONSI is granted subject to the construction conditions detailed in the record, including the implementation of U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service recommended mitigation measures which include the installation of bird flight diverters on guy wires to
RE|REG|A1273228|1319096|2718880|FCC|04/16/2021|2|minimize bird strikes and avoiding construction between March 1 and August 31. Hemphill, LLC must also comply with the Texas Parks and Wildlife Department (TPWD) general construction recommendations noted in the June 5, 2020, TPWD response letter, which
RE|REG|A1273228|1319096|2718880|FCC|04/16/2021|3|include scheduling any vegetation clearing outside of the general bird nesting season of March 15th to September 15th, properly designing and constructing power connections to avoid bird electrocutions, using erosion and seed/mulch stabilization materials
RE|REG|A1273228|1319096|2718880|FCC|04/16/2021|4|that avoid entanglement hazards to wildlife species, and no plastic mesh matting. TPWD also recommends the use of no-till drilling, hydromulching and/or hydroseeding. If erosion control blankets or mats will be used, the product should contain no netting
RE|REG|A1273228|1319096|2718880|FCC|04/16/2021|5|or contain loosely woven, natural fiber netting in which the mesh design allows the threads to move to allow expansion of the mesh openings. In addition, if any security lighting is required at the facility, Hemphill, LLC has volunteered to use
RE|REG|A1273228|1319096|2718880|FCC|04/16/2021|6|down-shielded, motion-sensored security lights.
