RE|REG|A1316364|1333053|2733564|FCC|03/26/2026|1|This FONSI is granted based on the information in the record stating that Vertex Tower will conduct all tree cutting during the northern long-eared and tricolored bats inactive season between November 1 and April 14. Also, a proposed single blast, if
RE|REG|A1316364|1333053|2733564|FCC|03/26/2026|2|necessary for the project, will be conducted between August 16 and May 30, which is outside the northern long-eared and tricolored bats pup season. Rubber matting will be used to dampen noise from the blast. Vertex Tower will also prohibit refueling
RE|REG|A1316364|1333053|2733564|FCC|03/26/2026|3|activities and storage of hazardous liquids within a 200-foot radius of all private wells and within at least a 400-foot radius of all municipal or community water supply wells. Best management practices such as silt fencing, armored fence, silt sock,
RE|REG|A1316364|1333053|2733564|FCC|03/26/2026|4|straw wattle, and/or coir log will be placed along work areas to prevent erosion and sediment from moving offsite. Vertex Tower will have an environmental monitor present to inspect best management practices once a week and within 24 hours of a rainfall
RE|REG|A1316364|1333053|2733564|FCC|03/26/2026|5|event of 0.5 inches or greater. Finally, Vertex Tower will comply with the conditions of all permits and authorizations it has obtained, including but not limited to the New Hampshire Department of Environmental Services wetland permit, Town of Thornton
RE|REG|A1316364|1333053|2733564|FCC|03/26/2026|6|Zoning Compliance Permit, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers New Hampshire Programmatic General Permit #6, and the New Hampshire Department of Environmental Services Water Quality Certification (WQC 20220404P-001).
RE|REG|A1277512|1333065|2733576|FCC|03/27/2026|1|NEPA resolved per FONSI letter granted March 25, 2026, file number A1277512.
RE|REG|A1277512|1333065|2733576|FCC|03/27/2026|2|This FONSI is granted based on the information in the record stating that The Towers will use downward-facing lighting on all ground facilities. For the protection of Indiana, northern long-eared, and tricolored bats, The Towers will only remove trees
RE|REG|A1277512|1333065|2733576|FCC|03/27/2026|3|between October 15 and March 31. The Towers will contact the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service Kentucky Ecological Services Field Office if potentially suitable gray bat hibernacula or roosting habitat is encountered during drilling or boring. The Towers
RE|REG|A1277512|1333065|2733576|FCC|03/27/2026|4|will also complete all excavation and grading activities and subsequent soil stabilization measures within one month. To prevent any negative impacts to offsite resources, sediment and erosion control measures - such as silt fences, straw wattles, and
RE|REG|A1277512|1333065|2733576|FCC|03/27/2026|5|other stormwater best management practices - will be implemented prior to, and maintained throughout, construction.
